Job’s Death is Great Loss to Apple and the Industry, Acer Says

-- B y   T i m   C u l p a n
-- 
2011-10-06T01:55:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-06/job-s-death-is-great-loss-to-apple-and-the-industry-acer-says.html
Acer Inc. (2353) , the world’s fourth-largest
computer maker, comments on the passing of  Steve Jobs  in a
written statement from spokesman Henry Wang.  “Steve Jobs was a person of great vision, innovation and
leadership, and had huge influence on the ICT industry in the
past 10 years.”  “His passing away is a great loss to Apple as well as the
industry, although the impact of his departure remains to be
seen.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tim Culpan in Taipei at 
